[b]Narrowing the skills gap, one chapter at a time.[/b]

Welcome to the [b]Master Discussion List[/b] for [b][url=https://www.meetup.com/bostonphp/events/297852222/]Career Essentials in Generative AI[/url][/b]. Begin by gaining access to [url=https://www.linkedin.com/learning/paths/career-essentials-in-generative-ai-by-microsoft-and-linkedin][b]Career Essentials in Generative AI by Microsoft and LinkedIn[/b][/url]. This learning path has been made available for [b]FREE[/b] for a limited time.

If you have not already done so, please post a brief update to [b][url=https://www.meetup.com/bostonphp/messages/boards/thread/54055597/]Introduce Yourself[/url][/b] which will acknowledge your commitment to begin this training opportunity. Next, we will conduct six weekly sprints to complete the six courses in this video-based certificate program as follows:

[b]Sprint #1[/b]: [b][url=https://www.meetup.com/bostonphp/messages/boards/thread/54055638/]What Is Generative AI?[/url][/b] (January 8 - January 14, 2024)

[b]Sprint #2[/b]: Generative AI: The Evolution of Thoughtful Online Search (January 15 - January 21, 2024)
[b]Sprint #3[/b]: Streamlining Your Work with Copilot (formerly Bing Chat/Bing Chat Enterprise) (January 22 - January 28, 2024)
[b]Sprint #4[/b]: Microsoft 365 Copilot First Look (January 29 - February 4, 2024)
[b]Sprint #5[/b]: Ethics in the Age of Generative AI (February 5 - February 11, 2024)
[b]Sprint #6[/b]: Introduction to Artificial Intelligence (February 12 - February 18, 2024)

Please access each Sprint Discussion Area (by clicking one of the Sprint links above) and post an update—including a link to that course's certificate of completion—once you complete that week's sprint.
